        "paragraph_index": 1,
        "text": "### Is Fe³⁺ consistently more stable?\n\n**Almost universally, yes.** Out of 42 ligands with comparable data:\n\n- **41 ligands** show higher maximum log β for Fe³⁺\n- **1 ligand** (2,2′-bipyridyl) shows **equal** maximum log β values (17.6 for both)\n- **0 ligands** show Fe²⁺ forming a more stable complex\n\nHere is a representative selection:\n\n| Ligand | max log β (Fe³⁺) | max log β (Fe²⁺) | Winner |\n|--------|:-:|:-:|:-:|\n| Catechol | 43.8 | 15.68 | Fe³⁺ |\n| Salicylic acid | 36.5 | 7.9 | Fe³⁺ |\n| EDTA | 25.1 | 14.3 | Fe³⁺ |\n| DTPA | 28.6 | 16.5 | Fe³⁺ |\n| Citric acid | 25.0 | 15.5 | Fe³⁺ |\n| Oxalic acid | 18.49 | 5.22 | Fe³⁺ |\n| Glycine | 10.0 | 4.31 | Fe³⁺ |\n| 1,10-Phenanthroline | 23.5 | 21.3 | Fe³⁺ |\n| 2,2′-Bipyridyl | 17.6 | 17.6 | Equal |\n| Fluoride ion | 6.04 | 1.4 | Fe³⁺ |\n| Chloride ion | 1.48 | 0.36 | Fe³⁺ |\n| Hydroxide ion | 11.81 | 4.5 | Fe³⁺ |",
